laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: Complete blood count and levels of electrolytes and glucose

laboratory_examinations.findings: Rapid qualitative test of creatine kinase was borderline positive.
Rapid qualitative test of troponin T was negative.
Echocardiogram showed hypertrophic cardiomyopathy with asymmetric septal hypertrophy, normal systolic function, and mild mitral regurgitation.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Follow-up echocardiogram two days later indicated no provocable gradient across the outflow tract.
